# Root .dockerignore — applies only to builds that use the repo root as their
# build context. Today that covers backend and control-plane. The web frontend
# and deployer images build from their own subdirectory contexts, each with its
# own .dockerignore, and are unaffected by this file.
#
# Keep repo-root build contexts small and free of host/runtime artifacts.

**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.venv
.git
.agent
.claude
.pytest_cache
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache
*.log

# Runtime data trees / secrets are never part of an image build.
instance/
workspaces/
sandboxes/
ops/env/.env
**/db/postgres/
